policy_rules.condition: SELECT COUNT(*) / TOTAL_COUNT * 100 AS metric_rate FROM airport_employees WHERE emp_code IS NOT NULL AND emp_code != ''
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Block: Downstream HR synchronization pipeline
policy_rules.description: Ensures every airport employee record has a valid employee code. Critical for security clearance and access control.

policy_rules.condition: SELECT COUNT(*) / TOTAL_COUNT * 100 AS metric_rate FROM airport_employees WHERE security_level IN ('L1', 'L2', 'L3', 'TSA_CLEARED')
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Alert: Immediate notification to Security Director
policy_rules.description: Validates that employee security levels match standard aerospace security protocols.

policy_rules.condition: SELECT COUNT(*) / TOTAL_COUNT * 100 AS metric_rate FROM airlines WHERE iata_code REGEXP '^[A-Z0-9]{2}$'
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Log: Invalid IATA codes to data_quality_issues table
policy_rules.description: Ensures Airline IATA codes follow the standard 2-character alphanumeric format required for flight boards and ticketing.

policy_rules.condition: SELECT COUNT(*) / TOTAL_COUNT * 100 AS metric_rate FROM aircraft_registry WHERE registration_no REGEXP '^[A-Z0-9-]{3,10}$'
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Block: Flight plan filing integration
policy_rules.description: Validates aircraft registration numbers (tail numbers) against international aviation standards to prevent regulatory fines.

policy_rules.condition: SELECT COUNT(*) / TOTAL_COUNT * 100 AS metric_rate FROM aircraft_registry WHERE status = 'ACTIVE' AND last_maintenance_date >= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE, INTERVAL 18 MONTH)
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Alert: Grounding risk detected
policy_rules.description: Ensures all active aircraft have a maintenance record within the last 18 months (or specific interval) to ensure airworthiness.

policy_rules.condition: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT pnr_code) = COUNT(pnr_code) FROM passengers WHERE flight_date > CURRENT_DATE
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Alert: Duplicate PNR detected for future flights
policy_rules.description: Guarantees that Passenger Name Records (PNR) are unique for upcoming flights to prevent booking conflicts.

policy_rules.condition: SELECT AVG(delay_minutes) FROM delay_records WHERE flight_date = CURRENT_DATE HAVING AVG(delay_minutes) > (SELECT AVG(delay_minutes) * 1.5 FROM delay_records WHERE flight_date BETWEEN DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE, INTERVAL 7 DAY) AND DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE, INTERVAL 1 DAY))
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Alert: Operational disruption detected
policy_rules.description: Monitors for a 50% increase in average delay minutes compared to the previous week's average, indicating systemic issues (weather, strikes).

policy_rules.condition: GRANT SELECT ON passengers(passport_number) TO ROLE 'authorized_security_personnel', 'checkin_agent'
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Audit: Unauthorized access attempt logged
policy_rules.description: Restricts access to sensitive passenger passport data to only authorized security and check-in personnel.

policy_rules.condition: SELECT COUNT(*) / TOTAL_COUNT * 100 AS metric_rate FROM baggage_handling WHERE passenger_id IN (SELECT id FROM passengers)
policy_rules.action_on_violation: Alert: Orphaned baggage record detected
policy_rules.description: Ensures every piece of baggage is linked to a valid passenger record to prevent lost luggage incidents.
